    "created_at": "2015-06-14T07:10:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-14T07:12:08Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If you're using Linux you should know that many popular window managers hijack your ALT key by default (for moving/resizing windows). For ALT to work in openra you must first release that key with dconf-editor (e.g. under org/gnome/desktop/wm/keybindings). You can't force-move any units anywhere without doing that. I just tested and can confirm that force-moving mechanics into transports works for me.\n"
  },
