    "created_at": "2015-06-24T04:40:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-24T04:40:52Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For KDE (assuming the use KWin - the default window manager for KDE):\nGo to \"System Settings\" (under \"Settings\" in the application launcher menu).\nSelect \"Window Behaviour\" (under \"Workspace Appearance and Behaviour\").\nSelect \"Window Behaviour\" along the left.\nSelect the \"Window Actions\" tab.\nSelect \"Meta\" instead of \"Alt\" as \"Modifier key:\" under \"Inner Window, Titlebar & Frame\".\n\n-- OR (for any use of KWin including under a KDE session) --\nRight-click on a window titlebar.\nSelect \"More Actions\" -> \"Window Manager settings...\".\nSelect \"Actions\" along the left.\nSelect the \"Window Actions\" tab.\nSelect \"Meta\" instead of \"Alt\" as \"Modifier key:\" under \"Inner Window, Titlebar & Frame\".\n\nThe \"Meta\" key is that key with a logo between \"Ctrl\" and \"Alt\" on most keyboards.\n"
  },
